> **Key insight discovered:** The rate-limiter uses a module-level `Map` that persists across tests in the same process. Tests now use unique emails via `uniqueEmail()` to avoid state bleed.
>
> **Zod v4 behaviour:** `.email()` validates before `.transform()` runs — so whitespace-padded emails fail validation (they're not trimmed first). Tests were updated to accurately reflect this.

